SFPM‑10 — Semantic Futures Projection Model
Sub‑Engine Architecture (Plain‑Text Specification)
=========================================================
SFPM‑10 is decomposed into five sub‑engines, each forecasting one semantic dimension:

SFPM‑S10 — Semantic Intensity Futures

SFPM‑T10 — Tier Futures

SFPM‑W10 — Influence Weight Futures

SFPM‑Z10 — Drift & Subzone Futures

SFPM‑Q10 — Qualified Interpretation Futures

Together, they produce the full future semantic state.

=========================================================
1. SFPM‑S10 — Semantic Intensity Futures Engine
=========================================================
Purpose
Predicts how the semantic intensity score will evolve over time.

Core Formula
Code
ds_i/dt = -lambda_i * s_i(t) + beta_i(t)
Discrete Projection
Code
s_i_future = s_i_now * exp(-lambda_i * dt) + reinforcement_term
Inputs
Code
s_i(t)
lambda_i
beta_i(t)
context
Output
Code
s_i(t + dt)
=========================================================
2. SFPM‑T10 — Tier Futures Engine
=========================================================
Purpose
Predicts future tier transitions using a discrete probability model.

Tier Transition Matrix
Code
P_i(t) = matrix of p_jk(t)
p_jk(t) = probability of tier j -> tier k
Update Rule
Code
tier_i(t + dt) = sample_from( P_i(t) )
Inputs
Code
current tier
role
drift level
context
Output
Code
tier_i(t + dt)
=========================================================
3. SFPM‑W10 — Influence Weight Futures Engine
=========================================================
Purpose
Forecasts how influence weights shift as meaning evolves.

Update Rule
Code
w_i(t + dt) = f( w_i(t), s_i(t + dt), tier_i(t + dt), context )
Normalization
Code
Sum over all i of w_i(t + dt) = 1
Inputs
Code
w_i(t)
s_i(t + dt)
tier_i(t + dt)
context
Output
Code
w_i(t + dt)
=========================================================
4. SFPM‑Z10 — Drift & Subzone Futures Engine
=========================================================
Purpose
Predicts future drift zones and fading states.

Subzone Mapping
Code
if s_i >= 80:      z_i = E1
else if s_i >= 60: z_i = EC1
else if s_i >= 40: z_i = C2
else if s_i >= 20: z_i = CN1
else:              z_i = N1
Inputs
Code
s_i(t + dt)
drift coefficient
context
Output
Code
z_i(t + dt)
=========================================================
5. SFPM‑Q10 — Qualified Interpretation Futures Engine
=========================================================
Purpose
Predicts how the qualified interpretation level will evolve.

Update Rule
Code
q_i(t + dt) = QFIM10( s_i(t + dt), tier_i(t + dt), z_i(t + dt) )
Interpretation Levels
Code
Critical
High
Moderate
Low
Minimal
Inputs
Code
s_i(t + dt)
tier_i(t + dt)
z_i(t + dt)
Output
Code
q_i(t + dt)
=========================================================
6. SFPM‑10 Master Operator
=========================================================
The full semantic future is produced by running all sub‑engines in sequence.

State Vector
Code
x_i(t) = ( s_i(t), t_i(t), w_i(t), z_i(t), q_i(t) )
Full Update
Code
1. s_i(t + dt) = SFPM-S10(...)
2. t_i(t + dt) = SFPM-T10(...)
3. w_i(t + dt) = SFPM-W10(...)
4. z_i(t + dt) = SFPM-Z10(...)
5. q_i(t + dt) = SFPM-Q10(...)
Final Output
Code
x_i(t + dt)
System Update
Code
X(t + dt) = SFPM10( X(t), context(t to t+dt) )
